description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity to join one of the most forward thinking, innovative and proactive Therapies teams in the East of England has arisen!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This vacancy will be working with the Physiotherapy and Occupational Therapy teams across the Colchester Hospital Site. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It offers the opportunity to rotate within therapies to clinical specialties such as Respiratory Medicine, Vascular surgery, Orthopaedics, Medical wards, Older peoples services and IRAS, the urgent care team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an experienced and dynamic Therapy assistant to work with the team to assess, treat and complete referrals for a wide variety of patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should have experience of working in rehabilitation ideally win an NHS setting, be enthusiastic and keen to work with the Therapies team to provide an excellent service. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to have good communication and organization skills, be a team worker and able to use your own initiative. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate would be educated to Foundation degree/ level 5 Qualification in Healthcare / Sport and Exercise Science or similar. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be supported by qualified therapists, working within a competency framework and will be given all necessary training for the job. You will manage your own workload and participate in team and service development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Christina Richardson, Professional Lead for Physiotherapy - Colchester Christina.Richardson@esneft.nhs.uk 07825364377&lt;/p&gt;
